{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/creating-jquery-plugin/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"bhansa's blog"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"7c0f9d0d-8857-54bb-9f95-7060bc5c00b5","excerpt":"Jquery has been used quite largely in many web projects because it gives you all javascript functions and commands wrapped in a nice API interface. For example‚Ä¶","html":"<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; \"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 24.324324324324326%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"jquery logo\"\n        title=\"jquery logo\"\n        src=\"/blog/static/39633fb2af89aa79926eb1e3d3c3f53c/fcda8/jquery.png\"\n        srcset=\"/blog/static/39633fb2af89aa79926eb1e3d3c3f53c/12f09/jquery.png 148w,\n/blog/static/39633fb2af89aa79926eb1e3d3c3f53c/e4a3f/jquery.png 295w,\n/blog/static/39633fb2af89aa79926eb1e3d3c3f53c/fcda8/jquery.png 590w,\n/blog/static/39633fb2af89aa79926eb1e3d3c3f53c/efc66/jquery.png 885w,\n/blog/static/39633fb2af89aa79926eb1e3d3c3f53c/c83ae/jquery.png 1180w,\n/blog/static/39633fb2af89aa79926eb1e3d3c3f53c/c1b63/jquery.png 1200w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n    </span></p>\n<p>Jquery has been used quite largely in many web projects because it gives you all javascript functions and commands wrapped in a nice API interface. For example: ‚Äújquery selectors‚Äù, used very heavily.</p>\n<p>Also, there were a lot of plugins which were build on top of jquery. for example: bootstrap‚Äôs modal, tooltip etc.</p>\n<p>Example usage of bootstrap modal:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"javascript\"><pre class=\"language-javascript\"><code class=\"language-javascript\"><span class=\"token function\">$</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"#target\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">modal</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"show\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>Whenver we use <code class=\"language-text\">$</code> instead of <code class=\"language-text\">document.querySelector()</code> it returns a jquery object which has some methods available like <code class=\"language-text\">.css(), .click()</code> etc.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Jquery object gets these methods from <code class=\"language-text\">$.fn</code> object</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>So, let‚Äôs say we want to write our own method and add it in <code class=\"language-text\">$.fn</code> definition so that every jquery object can also use that method.</p>\n<p>Let‚Äôs take a use case of <a href=\"https://css-tricks.com/snippets/css/drop-caps/\">Dropcap/s</a>. We want to apply a function on a jquery object which will basically make the first letter bigger in size relative to the sentence or paragraph.\n(<em>Something like we see in newsletters</em> ü§î)</p>\n<p>Let‚Äôs name this function <code class=\"language-text\">dropCap</code> and the definition will look somthing like this:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"javascript\"><pre class=\"language-javascript\"><code class=\"language-javascript\">$<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>fn<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function-variable function\">dropCap</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">function</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token comment\">// your definition goes here</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>We can use this function on any jquery object now:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"javascript\"><pre class=\"language-javascript\"><code class=\"language-javascript\"><span class=\"token function\">$</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\".some-element\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">dropCap</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>and it will execute whatever functionality we write in our <code class=\"language-text\">dropCap</code> function.</p>\n<h3>Protecting the <code class=\"language-text\">$</code> Alias and Adding Scope</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://learn.jquery.com/plugins/basic-plugin-creation/#protecting-the-alias-and-adding-scope\">Detail explanation</a></p>\n<p>Since the <code class=\"language-text\">$</code> variable is very popular among JavaScript libraries, we need to scope it and map it to <code class=\"language-text\">jQuery</code> variable by using a <a href=\"http://benalman.com/news/2010/11/immediately-invoked-function-expression/\">Immediately Invoked Function Expression</a></p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"javascript\"><pre class=\"language-javascript\"><code class=\"language-javascript\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token keyword\">function</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token parameter\">$</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  $<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>fn<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function-variable function\">dropCap</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">function</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token comment\">// your definition goes here</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>jQuery<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>‚è≤ Now, we can write some css for our <code class=\"language-text\">dropCap</code> class</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"css\"><pre class=\"language-css\"><code class=\"language-css\"><span class=\"token selector\">.dropCap</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token property\">font-size</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> 2.4em<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token property\">font-weight</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> 700<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token property\">margin-right</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> 5px<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>This will give the dropcap effect when we apply this class to first letter.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; \"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 29.72972972972973%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"dropcap css\"\n        title=\"dropcap css\"\n        src=\"/blog/static/bba2a56e42321e9762c6bc543de44818/fcda8/screenshot_dropcap_css.png\"\n        srcset=\"/blog/static/bba2a56e42321e9762c6bc543de44818/12f09/screenshot_dropcap_css.png 148w,\n/blog/static/bba2a56e42321e9762c6bc543de44818/e4a3f/screenshot_dropcap_css.png 295w,\n/blog/static/bba2a56e42321e9762c6bc543de44818/fcda8/screenshot_dropcap_css.png 590w,\n/blog/static/bba2a56e42321e9762c6bc543de44818/efc66/screenshot_dropcap_css.png 885w,\n/blog/static/bba2a56e42321e9762c6bc543de44818/c83ae/screenshot_dropcap_css.png 1180w,\n/blog/static/bba2a56e42321e9762c6bc543de44818/aeac4/screenshot_dropcap_css.png 1827w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n    </span></p>\n<p>Let‚Äôs finallly add the code for our plugin</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"javascript\"><pre class=\"language-javascript\"><code class=\"language-javascript\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token keyword\">function</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token parameter\">$</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  $<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>fn<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function-variable function\">dropCap</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">function</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    val <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">this</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">text</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n    first_letter <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> val<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">substring</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token number\">0</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token number\">1</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n    dropCapLetter <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token template-string\"><span class=\"token template-punctuation string\">`</span><span class=\"token string\">&lt;span class='dropCap'></span><span class=\"token interpolation\"><span class=\"token interpolation-punctuation punctuation\">${</span>first_letter<span class=\"token interpolation-punctuation punctuation\">}</span></span><span class=\"token string\">&lt;/span></span><span class=\"token template-punctuation string\">`</span></span>\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">this</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">html</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>dropCapLetter <span class=\"token operator\">+</span> val<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">substring</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token number\">1</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>jQuery<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>Above function reads the passed jquery object and updates the first letter of the paragraph as dropCap letter.</p>\n<h4>Codepen example</h4>\n<iframe height=\"265\" style=\"width: 100%;\" scrolling=\"no\" title=\"GRZPBRE\" src=\"https://codepen.io/bhansa/embed/preview/GRZPBRE?height=265&theme-id=dark&default-tab=html,result\" frameborder=\"no\" loading=\"lazy\" allowtransparency=\"true\" allowfullscreen=\"true\">\n  See the Pen <a href='https://codepen.io/bhansa/pen/GRZPBRE'>GRZPBRE</a> by Bharat Saraswat\n  (<a href='https://codepen.io/bhansa'>@bhansa</a>) on <a href='https://codepen.io'>CodePen</a>.\n</iframe>\n<p>Thanks for reading, I hope it was helpful in some way üòÉ‚ú®</p>\n<hr>\n<h4>References</h4>\n<p><a href=\"https://learn.jquery.com/plugins/advanced-plugin-concepts/\">Advance plugin concepts</a></p>","frontmatter":{"title":"Creating a jquery plugin","date":"September 24, 2020","description":"A jQuery plugin is simply a new method that we use to extend jQuery's prototype object. By extending the prototype object you enable all jQuery objects to inherit any methods that you add. - Jquery"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/creating-jquery-plugin/","previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/Creating-a-Covid-tracker-with-Vanilla-JS/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Creating a Covid tracker with Vanilla JS"}},"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/lazy-loading-images/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Lazy loading images"}}}},"staticQueryHashes":["2228355622","2841359383"]}